definitions.definition: To arrange ( troops, etc. ) in line for inspection or a parade .
To arrange ( facts, etc. ) in some methodical order.
To ceremoniously guide , conduct or usher .
To serialize an object into a marshalled state represented by a sequence of bytes that can later be converted back into an object with equivalent properties.

main_definition: To arrange ( troops, etc. ) in line for inspection or a parade .
secondary_definitions: ( by extension ) To arrange ( facts, etc. ) in some methodical order.
To ceremoniously guide , conduct or usher .
( computing , transitive ) To serialize an object into a marshalled state represented by a sequence of bytes that can later be converted back into an object with equivalent properties.
